Prompt 1: "Based on everything you know about me, what is the fastest way for me to hit my income goal? Limit it to one offer and one channel only."

The constraint forces ChatGPT to focus. No generic advice. One path forward.

Prompt 2: "Who is the single most successful person I should be learning from to make this happen? Give me one name."

Prompt 3: "Pretend you are this person. Create a 90-day action plan needing less than $1,000 up front and gets me my first paying customer as soon as possible."

Speed matters here. If you don't get momentum early, you'll quit.

Prompt 4 (the one most people skip): "Ask me questions one at a time until you find one thing holding me back. Then reframe it and give me a 2-week action plan to prove this works."
